To add a marginTop of '30px' to the second <Col> when the screen size is sm or smaller, you can utilize Ant Design's responsive grid system with the `useBreakpoint` hook or by applying conditional styling based on screen size.

Here's a simple way to do it using the `useBreakpoint` hook:

```jsx
import { Row, Col, Typography, Button, Grid } from 'antd';

const { Title } = Typography;
const { useBreakpoint } = Grid;

const YourComponent = () => {
  const screens = useBreakpoint();

  return (
    <Row justify="space-around" align="middle">
      <Col xs={24} sm={24} md={12}>
        <p style={{ color: '#5E4AE3', padding: '0' }}> زد من دخلك </p>
        <Title
          level={1}
          style={{ color: '#DDDCDC', marginTop: '-10' }}
        >
          قم بالمهام البسيطة وتقاضى الأجر!
        </Title>
        <p style={{ color: '#DDDCDC' }}>
          كل ما عليك فعله هو تقييم الخدمات التجارية عبر الإنترنت وسندفع لك المال مقابل كل تقييم تقوم به، <br /> فقط قم بعمل حساب جديد ويمكنك البدء في تنفيذ المهام على الفور!
        </p>
        <Button type="primary" shape="round" size="large" icon={<ArrowRightOutlined />} onClick={showModal}>
          سجّل الأن
        </Button>
      </Col>
      <Col
        xs={24}
        sm={24}
        md={12}
        style={{
          marginTop: screens.sm ? '30px' : '0',
        }}
      >
        <img src={heroimg} alt="[REDACTED]" style={{ width: "100%", maxHeight: '400px', objectFit: "cover" }} />
      </Col>
    </Row>
  );
};
```

**Explanation:**
- `useBreakpoint()` provides an object `screens` with boolean values for different breakpoints.
- We check `screens.sm` to determine if the screen size is small or smaller.
- If true, we apply `marginTop: '30px'` to the second `<Col>`, otherwise, no margin is applied.

This approach ensures the second column has the desired marginTop only on small screens or below.
